SIMPLE: practically
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Practically
<hw>Prac"ti*cal*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In a practical way; not theoretically; really; <as>as, to look at
things <ex>practically</ex>; <ex>practically</ex>
worthless.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By means of practice or use; by experience or
experiment; <as>as, <ex>practically</ex> wise or skillful;
<ex>practically</ex> acquainted with a subject.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In practice or use; <as>as, a medicine
<ex>practically</ex> safe; theoretically wrong, but <ex>practically</ex>
right.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Almost.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Practicalness</ent>⟦br⟧
